Third-party components pulled in at build time
----------------------------------------------

At configure time, `cmake/CommonAPI.cmake` downloads the following
third-party projects into the build tree. They are neither modified by
us in a way that changes their license, nor redistributed in source form
from this repository, but any binary distribution of this project may
ship compiled artefacts from them:

* capicxx-core-runtime  (COVESA, MPL-2.0)
    https://github.com/COVESA/capicxx-core-runtime
* capicxx-dbus-runtime  (COVESA, MPL-2.0)
    https://github.com/COVESA/capicxx-dbus-runtime
* commonapi-core-generator, commonapi-dbus-generator  (COVESA, EPL-1.0)
    https://github.com/COVESA/capicxx-core-tools
    https://github.com/COVESA/capicxx-dbus-tools

Additionally, a patched libdbus is built into the build tree:

* libdbus (freedesktop.org, dual AFL-2.1 / GPL-2.0-or-later)
    https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/dbus/
  Patched with the BMW/COVESA patch set shipped inside
  capicxx-dbus-runtime (see src/dbus-patches/*.patch in that upstream).

Unit tests link against:

* GoogleTest  (Google, BSD-3-Clause)
    https://github.com/google/googletest

If you ship binaries built from this repository, verify that your
distribution complies with the licenses above.
